-- Stocks in U.S. Drop, Led by Energy Producers as Oil Falls on Storm Outlook
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-06-28T14:15:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/u-s-stocks-drop-as-oil-falls-on-speculation-storm-won-t-hurt-gulf-output.html

          
          
             U.S. stocks dropped, led by energy
producers as oil retreated from a seven-week high on speculation
Gulf of Mexico production won’t be affected by a tropical storm.  
 The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index slipped 0.3 percent to
1,073.15 at 10:12 a.m. in New York. The Dow Jones Industrial
Average lost 23.58 points, or 0.2 percent, to 10,120.23. The
yield on the 10-year Treasury note slipped six basis points to
3.05 percent. The Dollar Index gained 0.2 percent to 85.483.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          June 28 (Bloomberg) -- Jeffrey Palma, global equity strategist at UBS AG, discusses his investment strategy.
     Palma, talking with Betty Liu, Jon Erlichman and Sheila Dharmarajan on Bloomberg Television's "In the Loop," also discusses the U.S. economy and bond market. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
